# Component Architecture

## File size (~100 lines)

- Target **≤100 lines** per file (excluding imports/exports). Hard max **150** before splitting.
- If a file grows, extract:
  - repeated UI → `components/vision/ui.tsx` or a new `*Panel.tsx` / `*Section.tsx`
  - local state + handlers → `use*.ts` hook in the same feature folder
  - types/constants → `src/lib/vision-*.ts`

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — 300-line page with inline table, filters, and modals
export function DashboardPage() { /* everything in one file */ }

// ✅ GOOD — page composes smaller pieces
export function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <>
      <PageHeader title="Dashboard" />
      <DashboardStats stats={stats} />
      <InspectionTable rows={rows} onReset={onReset} />
    </>
  );
}
```

## Component-based layout

- **Pages** (`pages/*Page.tsx`) — compose layout + wire props; no business logic duplication.
- **Feature components** — one responsibility (modal, drawer, panel, wizard step).
- **Primitives** — shared UI in `ui.tsx` (`Btn`, `Panel`, `Field`, `Badge`). Do not duplicate these styles inline.

```
src/components/vision/
├── VisionApp.tsx          # shell / routing state only
├── TopBar.tsx, Sidebar.tsx
├── *Modal.tsx, *Drawer.tsx, *Panel.tsx, *Wizard.tsx
├── pages/*Page.tsx
└── ui.tsx                 # reusable primitives
```

## Reuse before rewrite

- Check `ui.tsx` and existing `*Panel.tsx` / `*Modal.tsx` before adding new markup.
- Pass data via typed props; share types from `@/lib/vision-storage` or colocated `types.ts`.
- Extract the second copy of the same UI into a shared component.

## File naming (PascalCase + suffix)

| Kind | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| App shell | `{Name}App.tsx` | `VisionApp.tsx` |
| Page | `{Name}Page.tsx` in `pages/` | `DashboardPage.tsx` |
| Modal | `{Name}Modal.tsx` | `ConfirmModal.tsx` |
| Drawer | `{Name}Drawer.tsx` | `ManageProfilesDrawer.tsx` |
| Panel / section | `{Name}Panel.tsx` | `TrainedModelsPanel.tsx` |
| Wizard | `{Name}Wizard.tsx` | `NewProfileWizard.tsx` |
| Layout chrome | descriptive noun | `TopBar.tsx`, `Sidebar.tsx` |
| Hook | `use{Name}.ts` | `useProfileForm.ts` |

- One default export component per file; name must match filename.
- Use `@/` path aliases for cross-folder imports.
